    "We focus on \"articles\" users share over this network with each other.",
    "Each article on social media has a three-dimensional type (r, ν, m) indicating its reliability (r ∈ [0, 1]), veracity (ν ∈ {T, M}) and message (m ∈ {L, R}).",
    "The reliability specifies the likelihood the article is truthful instead of containing misinformation.",
    "If the article is truthful, it is more likely to argue for the true θ, whereas an article with misinformation simply provides noise about θ.",
